The paper deals with the problem of power allocation in compressed sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus on non-uniformly sparse signals suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the use of state evolution and approximate message passing techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI).
